docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, NoV. - The success of Miss Cholmondeley's clever story, "Jezebel," has been very marked. The in order to revenge himself on her mother. Precisely how this vengeance was to be accomplished is not very clear, unless the vengeful father imagined that the child would neceessarily live up to her name. If so, ho was disappointed, for Jezebel turned out to be a most admirable girl.
